---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BackAndForthSection from '../../components/BackAndForthSection.astro';

const title = 'Window Film Pricing | Window Film Philadelphia | Leading Window Film';
const description = 'Window Film Philadelphia offers the most competitive pricing for the best window film solutions in the Philadelphia area. Contact us today!';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical='https://www.windowfilmphiladelphia.net/resources/window-film-pricing/'>
  <section class="page-hero" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,30,90,0.72), rgba(0,30,90,0.88)), url('/images/window-film-pricing-philadelphia.png'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Window Film Pricing Guide for Philadelphia Properties</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <BackAndForthSection
  heading={'Window Film Pricing Guide for Philadelphia Properties'}
  body={'In order to obtain the most accurate, up-to-date window film pricing, it’s best to contact us for a quote. There are many factors that go into window film pricing, making every commercial and residential project unique. Window film often is a cost-effective alternative to other solutions but it can be a considerable investment for your upcoming project. Here is a basic guideline on window film pricing for Philadelphia properties.'}
  imageSrc={'/images/window-film-pricing-philadelphia.png'}
  imageAlt={'window film pricing philadelphia'}
  flip={false}
  altBg={false}
/>

  <BackAndForthSection
  heading={'How to Choose the Right Window Film'}
  body={'Because there are hundreds of different types of window films and brands, deciding on a window film can feel overwhelming at first, but it’s actually quite a simple matter. Finding the right film is all about identifying your goals. Are you looking for a way to save money on energy costs or is security a bigger concern? What do you hope your home/building will look like once the film is installed? Once you have your goals figured out, you can narrow down your options much more easily.'}
  imageSrc={'/images/window-film-pricing-philadelphia.jpg'}
  imageAlt={'window film pricing philadelphia'}
  flip={true}
  altBg={true}
/>

  <BackAndForthSection
  heading={'Calculating Actual Installation Costs'}
  body={'Once you’ve determined what type of film you need, the next step is to calculate the cost of the actual install. Though all installations vary because every building is different, there are generally three variables that affect the total cost: the cost to manufacture the film, the size/intensity of the project, and the quality of the service being performed. Cost of manufacture: Cheap films may cost less but usually don’t last as long since they’re just thin sheets of dyed polyester. Higher quality films cost more because they are made of more expensive materials like silver, ceramic, and high grade polyester, but produce better results. Project size/intensity: Larger projects typically cost more because they require a larger crew and more materials. Difficult installs can also be more tim'}
  imageSrc={'/images/window-film-pricing-guide-philadelphia.jpg'}
  imageAlt={'window film pricing guide philadelphia'}
  flip={false}
  altBg={false}
/>

  <section class="section-pad">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>General Price Estimates</h2>
    <p>Window film prices are usually calculated per square foot. Prices vary depending on the type of film and the brand. However, here are some general estimates on commonly used films: Spectrally selective: costs around $9-18 per sq ft; used for blocking out heat, glare, and uv radiation Low-e film: costs around $20 per sq ft; used for year round climate control and energy savings in dual climate regions Safety/security: ranges from $8-16 per sq ft; used for protection against forced entry, accidents, and inclimate weather Bullet resistant: costs around $125 per sq ft; used to strengthen glass and protect against impact, ballistics, and severe danger Security attachment systems: costs $2-5 per linear ft; used to attach security window film for increased impact resistance Decorative/frosted: cost $6-12 per sq ft; used for creating privacy or decorative features *Please note that prices vary and those listed may not be reflective of actual costs.</p>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="section-pad">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Work With Philadelphia’s Trusted Window Film Expert</h2>
    <p>Window Film Philadelphia is honored to be the trusted window film expert serving the state of Pennsylvania. Our team is happy to help guide you through window film pricing and can always give you a more accurate quote over the phone or during an on-site consultation.</p>
  </div>
</section>

  <section class="cta-strip">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Get Your Free Quote Today</h2>
      <p>Philadelphia&#39;s leading window film contractor. Contact us for a free consultation and estimate.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn--accent">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
